Hi Touseef, after looking at the request log, I am confident a solution can be reached since the FedEx response includes both the charge with VAT/tax and without VAT/tax. 
 &nbsp; 
 To give you an understanding about the situation. After a change in the way taxes are calculated on eCommerce orders in Europe, we are obliged to charge VAT on the orders
 based on the order’s destination country. And this is when WooCommerce comes handy where we have different Tax rates for each European country (for example, Greece has a VAT of 24%, Germany 19%, Sweden 25% and so on). 
 &nbsp; 
 Now, when we request a FedEx rate via API, the API returns our account’s rates and on top of that with our account’s (Cyprus) VAT which is 19%. On top of that, WooCommerce
 adds the respective country’s VAT which means the customer will pay double VAT. The customer should only pay their country’s VAT, not Cyprus’ VAT. 
 This is the reason why we need to use the rate from FedEx that does not include the VAT rate (totalNetFedExCharge).

